    "import json\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "import datetime\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n"
    "import pandoc as pandoc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Aaron's Code to get the list of Game Links:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "now = datetime.datetime.now()\n",
    "now\n",
    "url = 'https://statsapi.web.nhl.com/api/v1/schedule?startDate=2018-10-04&endDate=' + str(now.year) + '-' + str(now.month) + '-' + str(now.day)\n",
    "NHLSchedule = requests.get(url).json()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "424"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "i = 0\n",
    "j = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "GameList = []\n",
    "for i in range(len(NHLSchedule['dates'])):\n",
    "    GameLink = NHLSchedule['dates'][i].get('games')\n",
    "    for j in range(len(NHLSchedule['dates'][i].get('games'))):\n",
    "        GameList.append(GameLink[j].get('link'))\n",
    "        #print(GameList)\n",
    "        j += 1\n",
    "    i += 1\n",
    "    \n",
    "len(GameList)"
   ]
  },
